import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['temperature'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Temperature')
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['temperature'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['pressure'], label='Pressure')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Atmospheric Pressure (hPa)')
    plt.title('How does the atmospheric pressure vary over time in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['wind'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average wind speed in Seattle?')
    avg_wind_speed = data['wind'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_wind_speed, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Wind Speed: {avg_wind_speed:.2f} m/s')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.scatter(data['temperature'], data['wind'])
    plt.xlabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.ylabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between temperature and wind speed in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='temperature', by='month', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of temperature during different months in Seattle?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.suptitle('')  # Remove automatic suptitle
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Temperature')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
